  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-curry-pasty-with-mango-sriracha-dip/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced onion</strong>,<strong> chicken breast strips </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min on each side or until the chicken is golden</p><p>Once golden, add your <strong>curry powder</strong>,<strong> chicken stock mix </strong>and<strong> </strong>a couple of splashes of <strong>water</strong> and cover with a lid</p><p>Cook for a further 12-15 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-curry-pasty-with-mango-sriracha-dip/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dust a work surface with a small handful of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Unwrap your <strong>puff pastry </strong>and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>puff pastry</strong> into 1<strong> </strong>rectangle per person and add the <strong>pastry</strong> to a <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong>-lined<strong> </strong>baking tray (or two!), then set aside</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-curry-pasty-with-mango-sriracha-dip/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until the chips are golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-curry-pasty-with-mango-sriracha-dip/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, transfer it to a clean board and shred it apart using two forks – this technique is known as 'pulling'</p><p>Return the <strong>pulled chicken</strong> to the pan with the onion, season generously with <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> then give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>pulled curry chicken</strong></p><p>Divide the <strong>pulled curry chicken</strong> between the <strong>pastry</strong>, covering only one half of the rectangle[s]</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-curry-pasty-with-mango-sriracha-dip/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Brush a little <strong>cold water </strong>around the edges of the pastry (this helps to seal the pastry!)</p><p>Fold the <strong>pastry</strong> over the filling and seal firmly together then use a fork to crimp along the join and prick air holes all over</p><p>Brush the pastry with a little <strong>milk</strong> and top with <strong>half </strong>your<strong> nigella seeds </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), then put the tray[s] in the oven for 17-20 min or until golden and cooked through – this is your <strong>chicken curry pasty[ies]</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-curry-pasty-with-mango-sriracha-dip/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Combine your <strong>mango chutney</strong>, <strong>sriracha</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>mayo</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>mango-sriracha dip</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-curry-pasty-with-mango-sriracha-dip/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, drizzle a little <strong>olive oil </strong>over the<strong> salad</strong> and sprinkle over the<strong> remaining nigella seeds</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>chicken curry pasty</strong> with the <strong>chips</strong>,<strong> salad</strong> and <strong>mango-sriracha dip </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
